abstract: At least four people are killed, including members of the transitional parliament, after a suicide bomber blows himself up in a cafeteria in the central Somali town of Dhusamareb; analysts blame insurgent group Shabab for the attack. (S)t
lead_paragraph: At least four people were killed, including members of the transitional parliament, and at least a dozen were wounded after a suicide bomber blew himself up on Tuesday at a cafeteria in the central Somali town of Dhusamareb. Analysts blamed the Shabab, an insurgent group that has claimed responsibility for several previous suicide bombings.

headline.main: Somalia: Suicide Bomber Kills 4, Including Legislators
